-- SocGen Said to Hire Gert Van Rooyen to Head European Bank Equity Research
-- Sonia Sirletti
-- 2010-07-16T11:16:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/socgen-said-to-hire-gert-van-rooyen-to-head-european-bank-equity-research.html

          
          
             Societe Generale SA hired former UBS
AG managing director  Gert Van Rooyen  to head its European
banking equity research team, according to three people with
knowledge of the situation.  
 Van Rooyen, 38, resigned at the end of April after 12 years
at UBS, split evenly between South Africa and London. He will
start at Societe Generale on Aug. 2, said the people, who asked
not be identified because the appointment hasn’t been made
public. He will be based in London.  
 At UBS, Van Rooyen was a managing director in the asset
management division for the last two years. Previously, he
worked as a banking analyst covering French and Spanish banks
including  Societe Generale , BNP Paribas SA, Banco Santander SA
and Credit Agricole SA.  
 Van Rooyen, a native of South Africa, was a chartered
accountant there and graduated from the University of Pretoria.  
 A Societe Generale spokeswoman declined to comment. UBS
didn’t have an immediate comment on Van Rooyen’s departure.  
